00:20:16,974 --> 00:20:19,535
And because triple jumps are considered extraordinary,

485
00:20:19,716 --> 00:20:21,116
it means that with each jump,

486
00:20:21,537 --> 00:20:24,298
we can push the pose and personality further with each

487
00:20:25,339 --> 00:20:27,280
in the chain like you might do with an attack combo

488
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:27,880
in a fighting game.

489
00:20:28,361 --> 00:20:31,383
So it allows us to really kind of get more and more wild with it.

490
00:20:31,823 --> 00:20:34,806
But how wild we can get goes back to the one sheet

491
00:20:35,186 --> 00:20:37,408
and how showy they are in their personality.

492
00:20:37,888 --> 00:20:39,590
Since Fortune is more showy,

493
00:20:39,970 --> 00:20:42,692
she's totally within her character to do flips and spins

494
00:20:42,732 --> 00:20:44,834
and all manners of flourishes in her movement and poses.

495
00:20:45,174 --> 00:20:46,115
So if somebody comes up and says,

496
00:20:46,135 --> 00:20:47,016
I think that's too crazy.

497
00:20:47,236 --> 00:20:49,037
No, no, no, no, we established she is already crazy.

498
00:20:49,138 --> 00:20:49,398
It's fine.

499
00:20:51,971 --> 00:20:54,672
All right, so next, key framing and style,

