00:59:07,293 --> 00:59:10,394
Yeah, so out of combat is entirely animation driven,

1384
00:59:11,095 --> 00:59:12,595
which is why it was really important early on

1385
00:59:12,635 --> 00:59:15,937
for us to nail down, okay, at what frame do you turn by?

1386
00:59:16,077 --> 00:59:17,297
At what frame are you up to speed?

1387
00:59:17,357 --> 00:59:18,738
Because we want that consistency

1388
00:59:18,758 --> 00:59:20,999
and it's really easy with animation driven movement

1389
00:59:21,039 --> 00:59:23,100
to get a little sloppy with that

1390
00:59:23,160 --> 00:59:24,420
and not have it feel consistent.

1391
00:59:25,121 --> 00:59:27,221
So we locked that out early for in combat.

1392
00:59:28,002 --> 00:59:29,284
it is 100% physics driven.

1393
00:59:29,464 --> 00:59:31,186
You know, they want that ability

1394
00:59:31,206 --> 00:59:32,227
that if somebody's shooting at me,

1395
00:59:32,247 --> 00:59:33,028
I want to move out of the way

1396
00:59:33,068 --> 00:59:35,350
and not have to worry about a nice, pretty animation.

1397
00:59:36,031 --> 00:59:38,193
So we let that get right up to speed

